{
  "texts": [
    "We report these values in Table 1.",
    "The redshift values are the same as those used for the primary mass joy plot.",
    "For the same quantities, Abbott et al. (2023c) report M 1% = 5.0 +0.9 -1.7 and M 99% = 44 +9.2 -5.1: both values are in agreement with our findings for the low-redshift region, in which the mass distribution is dominated by the power-law-like feature.",
    "We do not quote the credible interval for M 1% for redshifts above 0.25 due to the dominance of selection effects in the lowmass, high-redshift region of the parameter space.",
    "The vetted region bounds below the credible interval for this quantity: we deemed the uncertainty estimate for z > 0.25 unreliable, and therefore opted to quote the median value only for reference purposes and to show that a growing trend is nevertheless present."
  ]
}